LICENSING

This project uses a dual licence structure.


1. Specification

The MediglyphCode specification, including the encoding format, triage model,
data schema, colour palette definition, and grid geometry, is licensed under:

    Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0)
    https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

You are free to share and adapt the specification for any purpose, including
commercial use, provided you give appropriate credit and distribute any
derivative specifications under the same licence.


2. Software

All source code in this repository (encoder, decoder, and supporting tools)
is licensed under:

    GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0)
    https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.en.html

You are free to use, modify, and distribute the software. If you modify the
software and make it available to users over a network (for example, hosting
a web based encoder or decoder), you must make the complete source code of
your modified version available under AGPL-3.0.

This licence was chosen specifically to ensure that MediglyphCode encoding
and decoding tools remain free for all users. Charging end users to generate
or decode MediglyphCode glyphs using software derived from this project is
not compatible with the intent of this licence.


3. Physical products

Manufacturing and selling physical products that carry MediglyphCode glyphs
(bracelets, tags, cards, stickers, pendants, or any other wearable or
printable form) is explicitly permitted and encouraged. No additional licence
or agreement is required for this use, provided the glyph is generated using
tools that comply with the AGPL-3.0 licence.


4. Attribution

All uses of the specification or software must credit:

    MediglyphCode, created by Peter Hughes
    https://poncdashphughes.github.io/mediglyph-code/


5. No warranty

This work is provided as is, without warranty of any kind. It has not been
clinically validated. See the paper and README for full details on the
current status and limitations.


